9h Edited 9 hours ago
Our third and finalchallenge for the #BuildwihAI Global Hack: Visualisation Challenge!

Details: The pandemic has hit many job types hard. But the impact is not distributed equally, most industries have seen their profits shrink and their workforce downsized, while others have thrived amidst a unique supply and demand shift.

We want teams to visualse that analysis and the trends of which job types that have been most affected, positively or negatively, prior to and over the course of the pandemic. Impacts can be assessed through any discernible mesaure; E.g market value, layoffs, remote working habits, reslience etc.

Requirements: No restrictions. All websites, apps, dashboards and other solutions will be assessed. Bonus points for teams that use Oracle Cloud credits.

Judging Criteria: There are two equally weighted judging criteria for this challenge:

1. Depth of insight into each job type
2. Quality of assumptions and approach

Shortlisting: Top 30% of teams will be shortlisted and presented to judges for ranking.

There is two hours left to join the hackathon! www.buildwithai.com

Philip Vollet
2nd
NLP Evangelist | 25K++ Follower
4d Edited 4 days ago
Elegy A Keras-like Deep Learning framework based on Jax and Haiku. Its in early stage but pure magic and super fast

$

GitHub https://lnkd.in/gaf3jzm

JAX is Autograd and XLA, brought together for high-performance machine learning research.

Why Jax + Haiku?
Jax is a linear algebra library with the perfect recipe:

Numpy's familiar API
The speed and hardware support of XLA
Automatic Differentiation.

The awesome thing about Jax that Deep Learning is just a usecase that it happens to excel at but you can use it for most task you would use Numpy for.

On the other hand, Haiku is a Neural Networks library built on top of Jax that implements a Module system, common Neural Network layers, and even some full architectures.

Compared to other Jax-based libraries like Trax or Flax, Haiku is very minimal, polished, well documented, and makes it super easy / clean to implement Deep Learning code!

Credits
Why not follow one of the authors on twitter
Check out Cristian Garcia (@cgarciae88): https://lnkd.in/gbEn6yM

__


#keras #pytorch #python #machinelearning #datascience

Retail and Consumer Products Industries Lead at IBM Supporting Transformation Leaders Deliver Bottom Line Results
1w Edited 1 week ago
The Covid-19 pandemic has impacted the health and welfare of so many. And at an industry level, businesses and professionals associated with the arts and fashion have been hit harder than most.

In the immediate term, we at IBM were concerned that the pandemic would also have a profound impact on emerging and future talent. To limit this and to ensure that this new group is protected and nurtured, we have worked on creating digital platforms to showcase their talent.

And so, we are delighted to announce that the next generation of creative talent from across University of the Arts London (UAL) - one of the most prestigious creative institutions in the world - will be showcased in one, curated space for the first time in history.

The newest names in art, design, fashion, communication, media and performing arts will be unveiled on the UAL Graduate Showcase a digital platform created with IBM launching to the public on Tuesday 28 July (18:30 BST). It has been designed to ensure everyone can explore and enjoy the breadth and depth of student work like never before.

#fashion #arts #talent #digital #response #covid19 #ibm #ecommerce #graduates #enablement
